HEADWORD: Caries
<hw>Ca"ri*es</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
decay.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Ulceration of bone; a process in
which bone disintegrates and is carried away piecemeal, as distinguished
from <xex>necrosis</xex>, in which it dies in masses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

